pageContext.description: A spiked ring of thin metal, extremely finely cast, from the circumference of the ring project three lines of short rather blunt spikes; each have being of four spikes; the spikes of each line are arranged in such a way that they insert the interval between the spikes of the next line.
pageContext.associations: Perhaps two spearheads (V) and two iron daggers.
pageContext.collection: E. R. H. Dicken,c/o 37 St. Georges Road,Wimbledon, S.W. 19,(August 1938)
pageContext.site: England,Essex,Wormingford,?,According to Mr. Sicken, two la Tene iron daggers were reported to have been found at Wormingford, and "perhaps with them" were found two Bronze spearheads Class V and a bronze "mace-head".
